description:
We are seeking highly ambitious sales traders to join our growing team based in New York.

Are you driven, energetic and extremely outgoing, this is the role for you. We are considering candidates with a strong character, an affinity for deal making and at least one year experience within the renewable energy space working with transferable clean energy tax credits.

Are you the natural born winner ready for your next challenge?

About Us

OTC Flow is a leading environmental commodity trading company with offices in Amsterdam, Paris, and New York. We provide trading liquidity in a broad range of financial-environmental instruments.

Our mission is to provide our global partners with access to renewable energy markets and to assist them in achieving their sustainability goals in an informed and intelligent way. Our network of partners is ever-growing and includes major actors across the entire renewable energy value chain.

About the Role

In your role as a sales-trader, your main focus will be to build your own client portfolio by closing transactions within the renewable fuel space.

OTC Flow acts as intermediary within over-the-counter markets so you will actively engage in outreach and prospecting through cold calling and client meeting. Your success in this role will rely on your ability to connect with clients both verbally and in writing as all transactions are bespoke and tailor-made.

Working closely with experienced sales traders and being supported with a variety of training sessions, along with close engagement in your professional development, OTC Flow enables your growth in knowledge and skills to become successful in this field. We strongly believe in meritocratic values so your growth within the company can be steep since more opportunities will come your way when targets are reached, regardless of tenure within the company.

Main Responsibilities
• Be responsible for achieving your own revenue (PnL) target;
• Proactively build your client portfolio through direct prospecting via cold calling and networking;
• Trade creation from origination until closing;
• Communicate with clients through phone, online, and face-to-face meetings to close transactions;
• Identify trade opportunities and support in executing them;
• Provide daily pricing and insights to market actors through messaging systems;
• Monitor markets and stay updated on financial news and developments;
• Promote OTC Flow’s services to increase the company’s market share.

About You
• At least a Bachelor's degree in Business, Economics, Finance, or a related field;
• 1 - 3 years of experience in B2B sales, brokerage, trading or similar client-facing roles;
• In-depth knowledge on clean energy tax credits established under the Inflation Reduction Act (IRA) of 2022, specifically around the legislative rules on creation and transferability of the credits;
• Proven track record of being involved in transactions of transferable clean energy tax credits;
• Strong drive to close deals and create impactful results for both OTC Flow and its clients;
• Very strong character, being proactive, resilient, and highly ambitious;
• Strong communication and negotiation skills;
• Commercial attitude and entrepreneurial spirit;
• Dedicated to achieving high targets early in your professional career;
• Comfortable working in a high-pressure environment;
• Excellent communication in English is required;
• Available for full-time on-site work at our NYC-based office.

What We Offer
• Hands-on, in-house training on industry knowledge and sales practices, directly provided by senior management;
• The opportunity to prove yourself quickly within a highly commercial setting, where a steep learning curve is guaranteed;
• A young and ambitious team with a strong focus on meritocratic rewards;
• Competitive remuneration, including a bonus scheme which is completely driven by your own results;
• Comprehensive benefits package, including health, dental, vision, and 401(k) options;
• 20 vacation days per year.

Remuneration

$70,000 - $80,000, plus an uncapped formula-based bonus structure with quarterly payments.

Base pay may vary depending on job-related knowledge, skills, level, and experience. It is only one aspect of the comprehensive and competitive compensation package offered to employees.

What's Next

If we have just described your profile, don't miss out on this opportunity.

The Recruitment Process:
• Submit your application with your CV;
• We will get to know you better through a pre-screening call with our talent acquisition team;
• We will invite you for 1-2 interviews.

We believe in the strength of our diverse team and are committed to creating an inclusive workplace where everyone can grow – together as a company, in teams, and as individuals. That's why we carefully consider all job applicants, fostering a culture that embraces everyone.g a culture that embraces everyone.

Disclaimer

Please note that we are unable to provide visa sponsorship for this position. Candidates must be authorized to work in the USA without the need for visa sponsorship now or in the future. Applications from candidates who require sponsorship will not be considered at this time.

